\": 1,\n  \"limit\": 50\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:49:36.924Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"openFileBrowser|useFileBrowser|FileBrowserContext\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\board-view\\\\components\\\\deploy-panel.tsx\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:49:38.584Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"isElectron|getElectronAPI|openFile|openDirectory\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\board-view\\\\components\\\\deploy-panel.tsx\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true\n}\nNow let me check how it's using the file browser in the deploy settings section and what the fallback behavior is when not in Electron:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:49:58.854Z] 🔧 Tool: Glob\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"apps/ui/src/components/views/settings-view/deploy/**/*\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:49:59.373Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\contexts\\\\file-browser-context.tsx\"\n}\nNow let me check how `getElectronAPI` works - specifically whether it throws or returns null in web mode, and see the deploy settings section for how it currently handles script file selection:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:50:13.140Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\settings-view\\\\deploy\\\\deploy-settings-section.tsx\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:50:13.872Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"export function getElectronAPI|openFile|openDirectory\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\electron.ts\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true,\n  \"-C\": 5\n}\nNow let me check the deploy script dialog to see if it also has file browsing:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:50:31.040Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\settings-view\\\\deploy\\\\deploy-script-dialog.tsx\"\n}\nNow I have a thorough understanding of the issue. Let me look at the image one more time and the exact UI flow to confirm:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:50:46.146Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\.automaker\\\\features\\\\feature-1770846400628-jpk0pwc8t\\\\images\\\\pasted-image-2026-02-11T21-46-26-341Z-1770846386374.png\"\n}\nLet me check the current state of the relevant modified files:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:52:09.210Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"openFile|openFileBrowser|Select Deploy Script\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\electron.ts\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true,\n  \"-C\": 10\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:52:09.847Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\server\\\\src\\\\routes\\\\fs\\\\routes\\\\browse.ts\"\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:52:11.059Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"Select Deploy Script|openFileBrowser|handleAddScript|handleBrowse\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true\n}\nThere's also a `deploy-button.tsx` component. Let me read that to see its file selection implementation:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:52:29.754Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\layout\\\\deploy-button.tsx\",\n  \"offset\": 120,\n  \"limit\": 80\n}\nNow I have the full picture. Let me check where the `openFile` web fallback actually produces the dialog shown in the screenshot:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:52:39.517Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\electron.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 1190,\n  \"limit\": 50\n}\nNow let me check how `getElectronAPI` determines which implementation to use and whether the web API also falls back:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:52:50.175Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"export function getElectronAPI|getGlobalFileBrowser|globalFileBrowser\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\electron.ts\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true,\n  \"-C\": 15\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:52:58.770Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"getElectronAPI|function getWebAPI|function getMock\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\electron.ts\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true,\n  \"-C\": 3\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:53:06.228Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\electron.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 1156,\n  \"limit\": 15\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:53:15.616Z] 🔧 Tool: Grep\nInput: {\n  \"pattern\": \"openFile|openDirectory|getGlobalFileBrowser|openFileBrowser\",\n  \"path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\http-api-client.ts\",\n  \"output_mode\": \"content\",\n  \"-n\": true,\n  \"-C\": 15\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:53:24.269Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\lib\\\\http-api-client.ts\",\n  \"offset\": 1068,\n  \"limit\": 25\n}\nNow I understand the full picture. The `openFile` in `http-api-client.ts` correctly passes `mode: 'file'` and `fileExtensions`. The file browser dialog IS in file mode. The actual problem is: **the \"Recent:\" section shows project folders (from `recentFolders`)**, and the initial path navigates to a projects directory with only folders. The dialog works correctly - files DO show when you navigate to a directory that contains them.\n\nBut wait - the user says \"deploy is still using project and folder instead of a file\". Looking at the screenshot again: the dialog shows the `Github2` directory content which has only folders. This is because the `initialPath` fallback goes to the default workspace directory (where projects live), NOT to the current project's path where deploy scripts would likely be.\n\nLet me check what `initialPath` is being passed:\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:53:40.730Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\views\\\\board-view\\\\components\\\\deploy-panel.tsx\",\n  \"offset\": 460,\n  \"limit\": 15\n}\n\n[timestamp:2026-02-11T21:53:41.574Z] 🔧 Tool: Read\nInput: {\n  \"file_path\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\DylanSmart\\\\Downloads\\\\automaker-pr\\\\apps\\\\ui\\\\src\\\\components\\\\layout\\\\deploy-button.tsx\",\n  \"offset\": 136,\n  \"limit\": 15\n}\nNow I see the issue clearly. Both `deploy-panel.tsx` and `deploy-button.tsx` call `api.openFile()` without passing `defaultPath`. This means the `http-api-client.ts` `openFile` method passes `initialPath: undefined` to the file browser. The file browser then falls back to `getDefaultWorkspaceDirectory()` - which is the projects directory (like `Github2`), a directory full of project folders, NOT the current project where scripts would be.\n\nThe fix is to pass `defaultPath: project.path` so the file browser starts in the current project directory. Let me now generate the specification.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\nWhen using the \"Select Deploy Script\" file browser, it opens to the default workspace/projects directory instead of the current project's directory. This forces users to navigate through project folders to find their deploy scripts, when the dialog should start in the current project directory where deploy scripts are typically located.\n\n## 2. User Story\n\nAs a developer using Automaker's deploy feature, I want the \"Select Deploy Script\" file browser to open in my current project's directory, so that I can quickly find and select my deploy scripts without navigating through unrelated project folders.\n\n## 3. Acceptance Criteria\n\n- **Happy Path**: GIVEN a user has a project selected, WHEN they click \"Add Script from File\" in the deploy panel or deploy button, THEN the file browser opens with the current project's directory as the initial path.\n- **Edge Case - No Project Path**: GIVEN the project object has no path, WHEN the file browser opens, THEN it falls back to the default workspace directory (existing behavior).\n- **Edge Case - Project Path Invalid**: GIVEN the project path no longer exists on disk, WHEN the file browser opens, THEN the browse API handles the error gracefully and falls back to the home directory.\n\n## 4. Technical Context\n\n| Aspect | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Affected Files | `deploy-panel.tsx`, `deploy-button.tsx` |\n| Dependencies | None |\n| Constraints | Both files use `getElectronAPI().openFile()` which passes through to `http-api-client.ts` `openFile` |\n| Patterns to Follow | `openFile` already supports `defaultPath` option, passed as `initialPath` to file browser |\n\n## 5. Non-Goals\n\n- Changing the file browser dialog component itself\n- Changing the server-side browse endpoint\n- Modifying how the file browser context works\n- Adding new file extension filters\n\n## 6. Implementation Tasks\n\n```tasks\n## Phase 1: Core Fix\n\n- [ ] T001: Add defaultPath to deploy-panel.tsx openFile call | File: apps/ui/src/components/views/board-view/components/deploy-panel.tsx\n- [ ] T002: Add defaultPath to deploy-button.tsx openFile call | File: apps/ui/src/components/layout/deploy-button.tsx\n```\n\n## 7. Success Metrics\n\n- The \"Select Deploy Script\" file browser opens in the current project's directory\n- Script files in the project are visible immediately (if they exist in the root)\n- No regressions in deploy panel or deploy button functionality\n\n## 8. Risks & Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Project path may not exist on disk | Browse API already handles invalid paths gracefully, falling back to home directory |",
